<div id="Idea_3713"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3713-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3713">Discontinue Medical Benefits for Congress and the Senate until Single Payer Health CARE is passed.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6316-4049">jolly.hobbit</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">3 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Many representatives work hand in hand to KEEP single payer health care from even being represented at meetings. And they also take huge amounts of money in contributions from HMO, Big Pharma and other medical groups. WHY should WE be giving benefits to representatives who work to keep the public from getting help?</div>
